
                   <p style="text-align: center">
                       <b>Title:</b> The Search page in the HCP System Management Console displays the current availability of each search facility and displays the current indexing status of the metadata query
engine. To refresh this information without reloading the page, click Refresh Now below the Indexing Status column in the data table.
Search facility availability
The following table describes the possible values for search facility availability.<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=185, y1=1170, x2=1516, y2=1495
                   </p>
                   <div align="center"><table border="1" class="dataframe">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: right;">
      <th></th>
      <th>0</th>
      <th>1</th>
      <th>2</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>0</th>
      <td>Search facility</td>
      <td>Value</td>
      <td>Description</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>Metadata query\nengine</td>
      <td>Available</td>
      <td>The metadata query engine is running on all HCP storage nodes.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>Metadata query\nengine</td>
      <td>Partial</td>
      <td>The metadata query engine is running on at least one but not all HCP storage nodes. This is most likely because one or more storage nodes\nare unavailable.\nIf this value persists while all storage nodes are available, contact your authorized HCP service provider for help.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>Metadata query\nengine</td>
      <td>Unavailable</td>
      <td>The metadata query engine is not running on any storage nodes.\nIf this value persists while at least one storage node is available, contact your authorized HCP service provider for help.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></div>
